MAHIKENG - The North West Government has made an about-turn on plans for a statue of President Jacob Zuma.The six-metre structure was to be erected at Groot Marico.Opposition parties and some residents criticised the project.READ: Spend Zuma statue money on Marikana investigation instead: DAThe sculpture was said to cost of R6-million, something the North West Arts and Culture department disputed. North West Arts and Culture Spokesperson Shuping Sebolecwe says this decision was not due to the criticism it received from the public Zuma was arrested in Groot Marico along with 45 other MK recruits in the 1960s while they were on their way to Zambia for military training.The North West government says it will call for proposals for a monument, an arts centre to benefit the community.eNCA